items.text:
üé¨** Medvirkende s√∏ges til kortfilm for **Foreningen Lige Adgang

I forbindelse med mit speciale, udvikler jeg en r√¶kke **kortfilm i samarbejde med Foreningen Lige Adgang**, der vises som en del af deres workshops og opl√¶g om **antidiskrimination **‚Äì optagelser i K√∏benhavn.

Vi s√∏ger medvirkende, der vil dele deres perspektiver ‚Äì **uanset om du har etnisk minoritetsbaggrund eller er allieret**, som vil bidrage til en vigtig samtale om trivsel, inklusion og ligestilling.

Du **beh√∏ver ingen filmisk erfaring** ‚Äì kun lyst til at bidrage til en vigtig samtale.

Det vigtigste er, at du har lyst til at dele dine tanker eller erfaringer og v√¶re med til at skabe film, der kan g√∏re en forskel.

**Fokus p√• tryghed og inkluderende deltagelse:**
* Filmene udvikles gennem workshops, hvor du som deltager har **medindflydelse og ejerskab** over processen og fort√¶llingen
* Vi arbejder med **l√∏bende samtykke**, og du godkender altid materialet, f√∏r noget deles
* **Alle medvirkende krediteres som medskabere** i filmen üé¨

Temaer, vi arbejder med:
üí¨ Hvad vil det sige at v√¶re en god allieret?
üîÑ Hvad hvis rollerne var byttet om?
üë• Oplevelser af inklusion og eksklusion
üß† Fordomme og bias i hverdagen

**Praktisk:**
üìç K√∏benhavn ‚Äì start/midt november 2025 (fleksibelt ud fra din kalender)
üïí To hele dage (ca. 6‚Äì7 timer pr. dag) ‚Äì mulighed for √©n dag eller en halv dag
ü•ó Forplejning er inkluderet

Vi √∏nsker et **mangfoldigt cast **og opfordrer alle til at melde sig ‚Äì uanset k√∏n, seksualitet, alder, etnicitet, religion, faglig baggrund eller funktionsevne.

Skriv til mig via **malene.juell@gmail.com** eller en direkte besked med:
* Hvilke(n) dag(e) i november, du bedst kan
* Gerne et billede af dig selv

‚Äî

**Malene Juell-Hansen** (specialestuderende p√• Film- og medievidenskab, K√∏benhavns Universitet)

I samarbejde med Foreningen Lige Adgang

üì¢ **OBS: Opslaget m√• gerne deles** ‚Äì kender du nogen, der kunne v√¶re interesseret, m√• du meget gerne videresende opslaget!

Hey there! üëãüèªüòÉ

I‚Äôm Freya Tingley ‚Äî an Australian actress born and raised in Perth. I started acting at 14, taking weekly classes with a dream of one day building a career in Hollywood.

Bit by bit, I booked short films, found a local agent, and put together a demo reel ‚Äî all steps that helped me make the leap to LA just before turning 18. Not long after, I landed my first major role as a series regular on Netflix‚Äôs Hemlock Grove, followed by Once Upon a Time, Jersey Boys, and DOTA: Dragon‚Äôs Blood.

Of course, it wasn‚Äôt all smooth sailing and the journey had its pitfalls and huge learning curves along the way. But those ups and the downs gave me something valuable; an understanding of what works, what doesn‚Äôt and the exact steps to take to keep moving forward. 

Most acting schools don‚Äôt teach how to build a career ‚Äî they‚Äôll say ‚Äúget an agent,‚Äù or ‚Äúnetwork: it‚Äôs all about who you know!‚Äù - but there‚Äôs never a clear road map, or step-by-step plan to help you to make progress, no matter where you‚Äôre at that.

I‚Äôm growing a community for actors who want a clear game plan, strategy, and support to level up and turn their goals into reality.

Come hang out with us! I‚Äôd love to meet you, hear your story, and help you move closer to your dreams.

üëâ Join The Business of Acting www.skool.com/the-business-of-acting-9301/about?ref=387a46092b6b412b82c1a78a4c1a240e

See you there! üòÉ
‚Äî Freya

items.text:
Be careful doing business with freelancers. Ask for references and contact them. Also ask for a photo ID and do not send a payment to anyone but them. This guy asked for a 1/2 deposit to hold the date. He spoke to me on the phone and through text many times and speaks as an experienced cameraman man. 

This person's supposed name is Steve Carter. He has a website listed and sends links to his prior work. 

Again never send funds to someone without real reference!

Casting call for a new series! 

Location: Studio City
Dates: Between November 16-19 (one day; most likely only needed for a few hours) 

We‚Äôre assembling a passionate and talented cast for the first shoot of a new original series. This project is being produced for social media distribution but filmed in a horizontal, cinematic format before post-production edits. These initial shoot days will serve as a proof of concept ‚Äî designed to build audience traction and secure brand partnerships and sponsorship funding for future episodes. These two roles will evolve into regular paid opportunities for our core crew. 

Compensation:
$125 per day, copy, on-set meals (lunch + crafty), and hands-on experience with a full professional production crew ‚Äî including cameras, lighting, and sound equipment. This is a great opportunity to expand your portfolio with high-quality material.

To Apply:
Please email partnerships@aurelianscollective.com with your headshot and resume/reel and we will send you the sides
 to tape. Thank you for your interest ‚Äî we look forward to hearing from you!

Woman Aged 39-59
Savannah, GA 
Rate: $300/day

Hey All!
This is a rush call casting for a non-union indie feature shooting this Sunday, 11/9 in Savannah, GA.  Please submit ASAP!  Those selected to audition will need to submit a self tape no later than Thursday evening. 

LAWYER (Speaking Role): Open ethnicity, woman, ages 39-59.  Well versed American immigration lawyer.  Has 7 pages of dialogue. Will need a strong actor who can handle a quick turnaround to prepare for Sunday's shoot. (Shoots one day)
Rate: 300/day. 

"Neither Nor"
Director/Writer: Ignacio Loizeau
Dramedy
Logline: A group of international friends try to find the most absurd ways to stay in the U.S. as their 90 days of unemployment after college comes to an end.

Please submit the following information to AlexisLeggettCasting@gmail.com using the the subject line "LAWYER" for consideration:

Name:
Phone Number:
City Located:
Height:
Availability to shoot this Sunday, 11/9:
Available to work local hire to Savannah, GA:
(lodging and travel will not be provided)
Reliable Transportation: 

Please include your headshot, resume, as well as a recent full body photo.  If you have a reel please send a link.

We will be reviewing submissions on a rolling basis- please submit ASAP!

Best,
Alexis Leggett

items.text:
Hi All, we @northeastproducers are branching out this year. We are testing the water down in the Plymouth, Torquay and Exeter area. We are only doing a short week, the week commencing 8th of December Monday to Saturday touring our Christmas Panto Jack and The Beanstalk to Care Centers, care homes and extra care schemes, trying to spread a bit of Christmas cheer to those in need of it üòä. We are looking for an actor to play the role of Jack.

If any actors aren't working or have various short contracts on in that period we would love to hear from you.
Fee is 550pw shows are performed between 11am and 3.30pm. A driver is required. All accommodation is sourced for you and paid for by the company and all fuel costs are covered whilst touring. 

If you are interested in working with us please send an email to info@northeastproducers.co.uk
Thanks we look forward to hearing from you üòä

Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch EINE hobbym√§√üige SCHAUSPIELERIN (w/d) f√ºr unser neues Projekt! Es wird sp√§ter noch ein Buch zur Staffel geben.

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :) Fahrtkosten k√∂nnen leider nicht √ºbernommen werden, aber f√ºr Spa√ü, Speis und Trank ist nat√ºrlich gesorgtüòä

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Bereits 12 Darsteller*innen + 2 Hunde sind Teil des Teams. Die Truppe scheint ganz lustig zu sein und einige Mitglieder kenne ich auch schon l√§nger.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

items.text:
# **CASTING CALL** (english version below)

Hey, wir suchen Schauspieler*innen f√ºr unseren Low-Budget-Studenten-Kurzfilm. Bei Interesse kontaktiert uns bitte per E-Mail: **[LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com](mailto:LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com)**.

Der Film wird an verschiedenen Locations gedreht, daher solltet ihr √ºber einen l√§ngeren Zeitraum (**mindestens eine Woche am St√ºck**) verf√ºgbar sein. 

**Unterk√ºnfte, Anfahrt und Verpflegung werden gestellt.**

** **

** **
## **Gesucht wird:**

**weiblich gelesene Person (S√§nger*in / Schauspieler*in)**

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**
* Musikalischer Hintergrund erforderlich (Sie sollten Gesangserfahrung und wenn m√∂glich Erfahrung mit dem Klavier haben) 
* Autof√ºhrerschein
* Deutsche Sprache C1

 

**M√§nnlich gelesene Person (Schauspieler*in)**

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**
* Autof√ºhrerschein
* Deutsche Sprache C1

 

**Drehtage:**

Anfang bis Mitte Januar

 

**Handlung:**

Die S√§ngerin Liv k√§mpft mit ihrer stagnierenden Karriere. Nachdem sie vor einem ihrer Auftritte zusammengebrochen ist, nimmt sie sich eine Auszeit mit ihrem Freund.

W√§hrend er glaubt, ihren Traum zu retten, versucht sie, sich von dem zu befreien, was aus diesem Traum geworden ist.

 

 

## **ENGLISH VERSION**

Hey, we are looking for actors for our low-budget student short film. If you are interested, please contact us by email: **LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com**.

The film will be shot at various locations, so you should be available for an extended period of time (at least one week at a time). 

**Accommodation, travel, and meals will be provided.**

 

 
## **We are looking for:**

**Actress/ Singer**

Aged 20-35

**Requirements:**
* Musical background required (you should have singing experience and, if possible, experience with the piano) 
* Driver's license
* German language C1

 

**Actor**

Aged 20-35

**Requirements:**
* Driver's license
* German language C1

 

**Shooting days:**

Early to mid-January

 

**Plot:**

Singer Liv is struggling with her stagnating career. After collapsing before one of her performances, she takes some time off with her boyfriend.

While he believes he is saving her dream, she is trying to free herself from what has become of that dream.

üé¨ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì BILINGUAL BACKGROUND EXTRAS (CHICAGO, IL)** üé¨

**Project Title:** *Letter 29*
**Type:** Independent Short Film
**Logline:** *‚ÄúLetter 29‚Äù is a docu-fiction short set during an exhibition of anonymous letters from displaced people, where the event‚Äôs host is confronted by his own unspoken connection to the stories.*
Learn more about the project on Seed & Spark ‚Üí[ [https://seedandspark.com/fund/letter-29#story](https://seedandspark.com/fund/letter-29#story)](https://seedandspark.com/fund/letter-29#story)

üìç **Filming Dates:** Nov 9, 10, 11
üìç **Location:** Chicago Grand Gallery 
 üïì **Time Commitment:** ~5 hours each day (exact call times given after selection)
 üé• **Non-Union / Unpaid**

We‚Äôre seeking **25-30 background extras** of **varying ages** ‚Äî **bilingual (English + any other language) strongly preferred.**

**Non-bilingual extras are still encouraged to apply**

**KEY BACKGROUND ROLES:**
* **Elderly Man** ‚Äì reads a heartfelt letter about an old neighborhood bar.
* **Young Kid (7‚Äì10)** ‚Äì plays with a toy airplane while their father reads a letter.
* **Father** ‚Äì adult male reading a letter from a mother about her first U.S. apartment.
* **Middle-Aged Woman** ‚Äì reads a reflective letter about her father‚Äôs sacrifices.
* **Young Man** ‚Äì reads a sentimental letter from an older relative.
* **Two Friends (20s‚Äì30s)** ‚Äì share a lighthearted exchange while reacting to letters.
* **Actor** ‚Äì performs a staged reading of a letter in front of an audience.
* **Couple (any gender)** ‚Äì quietly read a touching letter together.

‚û°Ô∏è *If not selected for a featured/key role, applicants may still be cast as regular background extras with non-speaking roles to enrich the exhibition setting.*

**Compensation:**
Unpaid. Snacks and refreshments provided on set. All extras will receive **on-screen & IMDb credit** and a **copy of the finished film** for their reel.

**Wardrobe:**
Elevated casual (neutral colors, no bright logos), slightly dressier for a museum/exhibition environment. Bring one backup outfit if possible.

üì© **TO SUBMIT:**
Please fill out the **Google Form here ‚Üí [**[[https://forms.gle/JX4nWxeaTaJdHiw4A](https://forms.gle/JX4nWxeaTaJdHiw4A)](https://forms.gle/JX4nWxeaTaJdHiw4A)**]**

üïõ **SUBMISSION DEADLINE:** **Friday, Nov 5 @11:59 PM**

Any questions or issues accessing the google form, email **letter29casting@gmail.com** 

No need to DM!

Tonight in Toronto: The Living Monologue

At The AWA Lab, acting training goes beyond performance. We explore how psychology meets the art of acting, helping you unlock presence, connection, and truth in front of the camera.

Tuesday, November 4th class focuses on The Living Monologue: From Performed Speech to Ongoing Experience - a practice designed to help you stay alive and reactive even when there‚Äôs no scene partner. You‚Äôll learn how to think in real time, trust genuine impulses, and make your performance feel spontaneous and emotionally grounded.

We‚Äôll also do a self-tape review, looking at how to watch your own work with awareness and use it as a tool for growth.

üóì Tuesday November 4 at 7:00 PM

üìç Midtown Toronto 

‚ú® First class FREE for new actors

Whether you are building your craft or preparing for your next audition, this class offers the consistency, insight, and real-world practice you need to grow.

‚û°Ô∏è Sign up here: 

https://forms.gle/3LqxHGM9mfAvtaoa6

üìΩ IMDB: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm10480327/

üì∏ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/isee.alina

www.theawalab.com

items.text:
LONDON UK

The five star, critically acclaimed full length play - You Won't Help Me, is back by popular demand. 

You Won't Help Me is a heart wrenching, fast paced, story written on real life experiences of domestic violence.

This play is not all doom and gloom though, there are also funny, laugh out loud, and heart warming moments too, just like real life.

This story has been touching people since January 2024.

ROLE 

DAVID

32-40 years old.

White/British/English accent.

Tall, handsome, charismatic, but has a manipulative, coercive, violent, aggressive side.

This character depicts themes of domestic violence, coersion, manipulation, physical aggression, and rape, the actor taking on this role, must be comfortable with this.

PAY

This project is equal profit share, no set fee.

DATES

Rehearsals start 11th Jan 2026 and will be every Sunday 11am-5pm.

Show run will be over 2 weeks, end of March/beginning of April.

Exact dates and theatres will be confirmed as soon as we are fully cast.

For previous shows and reviews, please visit https://distortedrebels.com/you-wont-help-me

To apply, please send us a message via Facebook or via our website asap.

We look forward to hearing from you!

Phoenix Benham

Distorted Rebels Productions.

üéÑ Casting Call: Princess Isadora ‚Äì The North Pole Experience, Liverpool.üéÑ

We‚Äôre seeking to recast a female-identifying performer aged 18+ to play Princess Isadora, one of the North Pole‚Äôs most charming and magical residents.

The ideal performer will have strong, confident acting ability and a natural warmth on stage. A confident singer is a bonus but not essential. Princess Isadora is playful, kind, and full of festive spirit, someone who captures the wonder of Christmas for every guest she meets.

---

Requirements:

Availability: Must be available on all of the following dates:
22nd, 23rd, 29th, 30th November
6th, 7th, 13th, 14th, 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd, 24th December.

Any additional day of rehearsal will also be agreed with the successful applicant. 

Location: Liverpool, United Kingdom

Experience: Experience in entertainment or performance is a plus, but we also welcome enthusiastic newcomers with a passion for performing.

Actor required in Liverpool.

Ideally someone with a car. 

Role : Traitors Game Hosts. The host is mysterious yet charismatic. They are in charge of picking the Traitors for the game, and then guiding the players through each step of it, until the winners are finally revealed.

Job details:

This Saturday - 8th of November 

6:30-9:30pm 

¬£130 plus an extra ¬£50 for extra travel requirements (North Wales), plus petrol cost also covered.

Total of around ¬£250. 

Ongoing work available throughout the year if successful.

Skills required:

-The confidence to talk with assertion and charisma to a group of people.

- Able to improvise within an ever evolving game. 

- Happy to be an authoritative figure within the room and ensure the groups attention is fully on you when needed.

Website : www.traitorspartyevent.co.uk

Please leave a comment or private message me if interested. Ideally with a Spotlight link or an Acting CV. 

Please also mention if you are a driver.

TRAUMASENSIBLES SCHAUSPIEL

(TRAUMA-INFORMED ACTING)

In den letzten Jahren ist eine neue Bewegung entstanden ‚Äì Trauma-informed Acting bzw. traumainformiertes Schauspiel. Dieser Ansatz ver√§ndert den Blick auf Ausbildung, Regie und die Arbeit am Set ‚Äì und er √∂ffnet einen Raum f√ºr echte Authentizit√§t ohne emotionale Selbstausbeutung.

Wie ein neues Bewusstsein Schauspiel, Schauspielausbildung und Kunst ver√§ndern und Heilung unterst√ºtzen kann

Von Daniel Urban ‚Äì Schauspieler, Schauspielcoach und Therapeut.

In den letzten Jahren entsteht eine neue Haltung: traumainformiertes Schauspiel (auch: traumasensibles bzw. traumabewusstes Schauspiel). Sie anerkennt, dass Emotion nicht beliebig abrufbar ist, dass jede Darstellerin und jeder Darsteller Biografie und Verletzlichkeit mitbringt ‚Äì und dass Sicherheit vor Intensit√§t kommen sollte, ohne k√ºnstlerische Tiefe zu verlieren.

Einleitung ‚Äì Ein Wandel beginnt im Bewusstsein.

Jahrzehntelang wurde Schauspiel oft als Disziplin verstanden, die absolute Hingabe verlangt ‚Äì emotional, k√∂rperlich, seelisch. Schauspieler:innen sollten ‚Äûfunktionieren‚Äú, Gef√ºhle auf Knopfdruck produzieren und die eigene Grenze zugunsten der Kunst aufgeben. In Teilen der Ausbildung kursierte lange die Idee, man m√ºsse junge Schauspielstudent:innen erst ‚Äûbrechen‚Äú, um sie dann neu ‚Äûaufzubauen‚Äú. Heute wird immer klarer: Dieser Ansatz kann verletzen ‚Äì menschlich und k√ºnstlerisch.

Artikel hier weiterlesen: https://danielurban.de/blog-traumainformiertes-schauspiel/

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply to advocacy groups that align with your film's message for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

items.text:
Howdy Denver film community! We‚Äôre Wasteland of Wonder, a boutique film production company based here in Denver, CO that focuses on community building through creative collaboration. We‚Äôre seeking an actor for a music video and would love to engage with some new, local talent. Email us at wastelandofwonder@gmail.com for information about auditions!

TITLE: ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt Think‚Äù 

GENRE: Gothic industrial music video 

SYNOPSIS: ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt Think‚Äù explores themes of control and alienation both societally and personally with evocative and surreal imagery.  Our protagonist, Ezra, is an audience member at a surrealist concert- who slowly loses themself in the music. In a B plot we see manufacturers, men in a unique blend of industrial and medical garb, grooming and preparing Ezra for some kind of operation.  

CHARACTER: Ezra, (20s), feels alienated and unable to connect with others.  Ezra‚Äôs arc in the video is one of surrender and vulnerability, giving in to the pressures of everyone around them. 

This role is open casting for Men and Nonbinary actors of any race. Ideally the actor would be very skilled in physical work and have a dramatic background. 

PRODUCTION INFO

PRODUCTION COMPANY: Wasteland of Wonder (wastelandofwonder.com)

PRODUCTION TYPE: Music Video

CONTACT INFO: wastelandofwonder@gmail.com

COMPENSATION: The role will be compensated, rate TBD 

AUDITION INFORMATION: No audition, just send us a resume and reel :). Email us for further information. 

SHOOT SCHEDULE: Mid November 

FILMING LOCATION: Denver Metro & the Front Range

items.text:
CASTING CALL: Protesters Voiceover ‚Äì ‚ÄúDenied Care‚Äù Series

Project Title: Denied Care
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment, Inc.
Type: Voiceover (Non-Union / Indie Production)
Location: Remote Recording Accepted
Compensation: paid 
Recording Date: November 15th

Looking for 3 voiceovers

---

PROJECT OVERVIEW

Denied Care is a scripted drama following Ava Winters, a young woman denied life-saving treatment by a broken healthcare system. The story exposes the real human cost of bureaucratic neglect through emotional, defiant, and darkly comedic storytelling.

Short Film feature a pivotal protest montage ‚Äî where voices from across the nation rise in solidarity. This casting call is for those protester voices ‚Äî raw, real, and unapologetic.

---

ROLE: PROTESTER VOICEOVER (MULTIPLE TALENTS)

Gender: Any
Age Range: 18‚Äì65
Accent: Open ‚Äî diverse voices encouraged
Tone: Authentic, passionate, emotional, and real
Vocal Quality:

Gritty, tired, but determined

Feels like you‚Äôve lived it ‚Äî not ‚Äúperformed‚Äù it

Think real activists, not voice actors

Examples of Lines (for audition):

‚ÄúWe are not invisible!‚Äù

‚ÄúYou can‚Äôt deny care to the living!‚Äù

‚ÄúWe‚Äôre sick, not silent!‚Äù

‚ÄúEvery denial has a name!‚Äù

‚ÄúWe are the denied ‚Äî and we‚Äôre not backing down!‚Äù

(Actors may be asked to record crowd-style chants, overlapping dialogue, and emotional reactions.)

---

RECORDING NOTES

Please record clean audio (WAV or MP3) with minimal background noise.

Multiple takes with varying energy levels are encouraged.

Shouting, chanting, and overlapping crowd energy welcome.

items.text:
Casting Call: Singer-Songwriter for Music Video (Unpaid)

Production Title: Christmas Music video 
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.
Type: Music Video
Location: Colorado (exact location TBD)
Filming Dates: late November early December 2025
Compensation: Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

---

About the Project

Superstar TV Entertainment Inc. is producing a heartfelt, cinematic music video featuring a singer-songwriter whose performance captures raw emotion and authenticity. This project is designed to highlight both the artist and visual storytelling ‚Äî similar in tone to Lewis Capaldi, Adele, or Noah Kahan.

The final video will be professionally shot and released across Superstar TV platforms, YouTube, and social media for maximum exposure.

---

Roles

üé§ Lead Artist / Singer-Songwriter (Principal Role)

Gender: Open to all

Age Range: 18‚Äì35

Vocal Style: Pop, acoustic, R&B, soul, or indie-folk preferred

Description: Emotionally expressive performer with on-camera presence. Must be comfortable lip-syncing to playback or performing live vocals. Guitar or piano ability is a plus.

Requirements: Must be reliable, punctual, and open to creative collaboration.

---

Supporting Roles (If applicable)

Love Interest: Ages 20‚Äì35, expressive and able to convey emotional connection.

Extras: Audience members, friends, or background talent for performance scenes.

---

Compensation

Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

You‚Äôll receive:

A professional-quality music video for your reel

IMDB credit under Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.

Networking opportunity for future paid productions

---

Submission Instructions

Please submit the following to tyler.schachtceo@outlook.com with the subject line:
Christmas Music Video ‚Äì [Your Name]‚Äù

Include:

Headshot or clear photo

Short performance clip or demo reel (YouTube or social media link accepted)

Short bio or resume

Contact information (email + phone number)

Hi! I'm Colleen and I'm a private voice & acting teacher, and the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We are currently offering free VIRTUAL lessons to meet new students who may be interested in continuing professional individualized coaching!

We currently offer lessons in voice, piano, violin, viola, cello, guitar, and acting, along with 2 in-person recitals each year in 4 Midwestern states. Each of our teachers is committed to providing personalized instruction to help every student reach their goals. Whether you‚Äôre preparing for auditions, trying to book professional gigs, or simply looking to grow as a performer, our teachers are here to support and encourage you every step of the way!

If you‚Äôd like to get started, fill out this form, and we‚Äôll match you with the teacher who‚Äôs the best fit for your goals and interests. [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

This isn‚Äôt your average Christmas Carol‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs a witty, fast-paced, and heartfelt reimagining of the holiday classic. Ebenezer Scrooge still faces ghosts, regrets, and redemption, but along the way you‚Äôll be treated to:

Don‚Äôt forget to grab your tickets!

Georgetown Little Theatre proudly presents ***A Telling of The Christmas Carol*** ‚Äî running **November 27th to December 6th, 2025**.

This isn‚Äôt your average Christmas Carol‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs a witty, fast-paced, and heartfelt reimagining of the holiday classic. Ebenezer Scrooge still faces ghosts, regrets, and redemption, but along the way you‚Äôll be treated to:
Laughs, Ghosts who bicker like overworked employees, Marley fumbling through haunting ‚Äúprotocols‚Äù And the timeless spirit of generosity and hope.

You might laugh, you might cry ‚Äî but one thing is certain: you‚Äôll have a fantastic time!

**62% sold out! ‚Äî don‚Äôt wait!** 

Support local theatre
Support our amazing performers
Support the arts in our community

Tickets are on sale now ‚Äî get yours before they‚Äôre gone!

items.text:
Hi everyone! I just wanted to invite you all and share details of the second edition of the Wine Dark Short Film Festival, which will be taking place at ActOne Cinema in Acton (West London) on 15 November 2025.

The Wine Dark Short Film Festival (WDSFF) is London's first film festival dedicated exclusively to mental health, disability and neurodiversity*. Now in its second year, WDSFF celebrates often-unsung voices in the film industry. The festival will proudly showcase short films that are either created by D/deaf, disabled, or neurodiverse filmmakers or explore themes related to mental health, disability, and exclusion.

We'll be screening over 20 international films, as well as offering a neurodivergent-friendly networking session, and Q&As with film industry professionals, including Sarah Leigh (Inclusivity Films) and Bonnie MacBird (screenwriter/director).

You can get tickets here: 

[https://www.actonecinema.co.uk/movie/wine-dark-short-film-festival](https://www.actonecinema.co.uk/movie/wine-dark-short-film-festival)

items.text:
JOIN US FOR***THE FORCE: The Michael Watson Story!*** ü•ä  

We‚Äôve got several key shoot days coming up in **November 2025**, and we‚Äôd love for you to join us as **supporting artists**:

üìç **Sat 8 Nov ‚Äì Aylesbury Crown Court**Michael Watson‚Äôs landmark court case vs the BBBofC ‚Äî courtroom attendees & press needed.

üìç **Sun 9 Nov ‚Äì St Bartholomew‚Äôs Hospital, London** The emotional scene where *Muhammad Ali visits Michael Watson* ‚Äî paparazzi & onlookers needed!

üìç **Thu 13 Nov ‚Äì Constitution Hill (near Buckingham Palace)**
Michael‚Äôs incredible **London Marathon** moment ‚Äî runners & supporters for the finish line!

üìç **Fri 14 Nov ‚Äì Oatlands Park Hotel, Surrey** The infamous press conference between **Chris Eubank Sr. & Michael Watson** ‚Äî we need around 20 people to play press!

üìç **Sat 15 & Sun 16 Nov ‚Äì Tannery Studios, Woking** Two HUGE boxing days ‚Äî come be part of the crowd and bring the energy!

This is an **independent film (expenses only)**, but it‚Äôll be an unforgettable experience ‚Äî and everyone joining will also get an invite to the **Leicester Square red carpet premiere!** üéüÔ∏è‚ú®

üìß **To join:**email casting@magnificentfilms.co.uk with the dates you can make, and we‚Äôll send all the info & dress code.

üìç **Thu 13 Nov ‚Äì Constitution Hill (near Buckingham Palace)**
Michael‚Äôs incredible **London Marathon** moment ‚Äî runners & supporters for the finish line!

üìç **Fri 14 Nov ‚Äì Oatlands Park Hotel, Surrey** The infamous press conference between **Chris Eubank Sr. & Michael Watson** ‚Äî we need around 20 people to play press!

üìç **Sat 15 & Sun 16 Nov ‚Äì Tannery Studios, Woking** Two HUGE boxing days ‚Äî come be part of the crowd and bring the energy!

This is an **independent film (expenses only)**, but it‚Äôll be an unforgettable experience ‚Äî and everyone joining will also get an invite to the **Leicester Square red carpet premiere!** üéüÔ∏è‚ú®

üìß **To join:**email casting@magnificentfilms.co.uk with the dates you can make, and we‚Äôll send all the info & dress code.

items.text:
Casting Brief

We are casting a drama scene that plays out in a VR training environment for security service industry personnel. This is a high drama realistic video, where you interact directly with the audience, looking into the lens, in the same way as in PeepShow.  Please read the casting breakdowns and only apply if you meet the requirements and are available on that shoot date. Please do not apply if you‚Äôre not. Full details on the application below.  We can't repsond to "interested". Please follow the details below. Thanks in advance.

Shoot Date: 19th November.  (locked no deviation on the date)

Shoot Times: Approx 8am - 7pm

Location:    Romford

Nearest Tube: Chadwell Heath (Elizabeth line)

Rick - Male 25-45 Any Ethnicity  - Security officer - calm and organised. Working security at high profile events. Someone who can be relied on. Professional look. Interacting with the lead

Steve  - Male 25-45 Any Ethnicity Security officer - lazy uninterested in taking things overly seriously. Does the bare minimum. Smart look overall. Interacting with the lead

Commander Alan - Male 35-50 Any Ethnicity - ex military type. Knows the seriousness of the job and what it takes to keep people safe. Interacting with the lead

Kelly - Female 24-35 Any Ethnicity - guest at the event, is involved in a high stress situation when during an attack she is separate from a loved one. Interacting with the lead

Stef - Female  25-45 Any Ethnicity - guest at the event, is involved in a high stress situation when during an attack she is separate from a loved one. Interacting with the lead

Ali - Waiter / waitress / host  Male / Female  25-45 Any Ethnicity - high end service industry professional working hard in the venue. Gets caught up in a high stress situation and tries to get past / around the lead

Danny - Photographer  Male / Female 25-45 a photographer with kit who is pushy about gaining access to certain areas, with or without rules being broken. Interacting with the lead

X - Male / Female 25-45 - this person is either a red herring or a criminal. Could they be doing something wrong, or just in the wrong place?  Interacting with the lead

The singer  - Male / Female 25-45 Any Ethnicity - performing on the main stage, solo gig to the audience, it‚Äôs your concert, your gig. Will be lip syncing to a couple of tracks while the experience plays out.

To apply please send an email with Subject Title ‚ÄúAudition T19 (and include the role‚Äù eg  Audition T19 Danny

Please send a brief email stating your experience and why you're suited to the role. 

Please include a recent headshot and full length.

Please include a youtube link to your showreel, if you don‚Äôt have a showreel a link to a brief monologue with an intro to who you are.

Please send submissions to info@ultrareality.co.uk

Paid: ¬£175

Use: private online in training app only. Not public.

Credits will be given

The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency
About Us
The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency is a proudly South African-based casting and extras coordination agency, operating since 2018. We work behind the scenes to help bring incredible stories to life ‚Äî connecting talent with opportunity across film, television, and digital productions.
Our Talent
With a growing database of over 1,000 talented actors, actresses, artists, and models, we take pride in representing individuals who continue to make us proud on some of the biggest local and international stages. Our artists have been featured in productions on Netflix, DStv, BET, and many more renowned platforms.
What We Do
We specialize in supplying background extras, featured roles, models, and performing artists for feature films, commercials, music videos, and television projects. Our experienced coordination team ensures every production finds the perfect fit for its creative vision.
Join Us

items.text:
Hi All, we @northeastproducers are branching out this year. We are testing the water down in the Plymouth, Torquay and Exeter area. We are only doing a short week, the week commencing 8th of December Monday to Saturday touring our Christmas Panto Jack and The Beanstalk to Care Centers, care homes and extra care schemes, trying to spread a bit of Christmas cheer to those in need of it üòä. We are looking for an actor to play the role of Jack.

If any actors aren't working or have various short contracts on in that period we would love to hear from you.
Fee is 550pw shows are performed between 11am and 3.30pm. A driver is required. All accommodation is sourced for you and paid for by the company and all fuel costs are covered whilst touring. 

If you are interested in working with us please send an email to info@northeastproducers.co.uk
Thanks we look forward to hearing from you üòä

üéÑ Casting Call: Princess Isadora ‚Äì The North Pole Experience, Liverpool.üéÑ

We‚Äôre seeking to recast a female-identifying performer aged 18+ to play Princess Isadora, one of the North Pole‚Äôs most charming and magical residents.

The ideal performer will have strong, confident acting ability and a natural warmth on stage. A confident singer is a bonus but not essential. Princess Isadora is playful, kind, and full of festive spirit, someone who captures the wonder of Christmas for every guest she meets.

---

Requirements:

Availability: Must be available on all of the following dates:
22nd, 23rd, 29th, 30th November
6th, 7th, 13th, 14th, 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd, 24th December.

Any additional day of rehearsal will also be agreed with the successful applicant. 

Location: Liverpool, United Kingdom

Experience: Experience in entertainment or performance is a plus, but we also welcome enthusiastic newcomers with a passion for performing.

Personality: Must embody the spirit of Christmas and bring the character to life with warmth and confidence.

Pay:

Rehearsals paid hourly at the National Minimum Wage (NMW) for your age group.

Performance days paid at ¬£160 per day, depending on role and experience.

Lunch and refreshments provided on all performance days.

Cast members also receive complimentary tickets for our Friends & Family Day, plus staff discount in our on-site merchandise shop.

---

Application Details:
Please email casting@thenorthpoleexperience.co.uk with:

1. Full name and contact details (phone number, email address)

2. Role you‚Äôre interested in auditioning for

3. Relevant performance or entertainment experience (if applicable)

4. Confirmation of full availability for the listed dates

5. Recent headshot(s) and/or showreel

---

Help us bring the magic of Christmas to life at The North Pole Experience ‚Äî we can‚Äôt wait to make magic with you! ‚ú®

Open Call In Person Auditions Mon. & Tues. Nov 10 & 11 at 7pm for The 39 Steps by Patrick Barlow, Directed by Liz Bove. Performances: Jan. 9-18: Fri. & Sat. 8pm & Sundays 2pm + 2pm Matinee Sat. 1/17. More Details @ [https://www.facebook.com/share/17ZdspnYwH/](https://www.facebook.com/share/17ZdspnYwH/) Auditions @HeightsPlayers 26 Willow Place Brooklyn, NY 11201. (718) 237-2752. Please bring a headshot and resume, sides available on website. Please be sure to be available for in person call backs. NO pay.

CHARACTER BREAKDOWN:

**A familiarity with the Hitchcock film, The 39 Steps (1935), is highly recommended as the play is a direct spoof on the film. You may find this on ****[Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jfVtoPN3BVk)****.**
**Richard Hannay:** 30s-40s. A Hitchcock-esque suave, dashing, debonaire fellow. A physically adept comedian. Must be able to do a British accent. 

**Annabella Schmidt:** 20s-30s. An exotic and intriguing spy. Must be able to do a German accent. Actress will also play Margaret. 

**Pamela**: 20s-30s. The quintessential Hitchcock-esqe leading lady. She is bold, emotionally and intellectually intelligent. British accent required. 

**Margaret**: 20s-30s. The wife of a stern religious Scottish farmer. Scottish accent required. Actress will also play Annabella. 

**Clown #1 **& **Clown #2:** Any age, gender, race. Vivacious and debonair, both clowns expertly execute multiple male and female roles with skillful physical comedic skills.  English and Scottish accents a must.

Theatre Online Ltd. are still looking for actors to join them for Pantomime 2025. 

This is for PAID, UK Wide school tours. 

Friday 21st November ‚Äì Friday 19th December 2025.

They are ideally looking for drivers aged 25 and above, although the ability to drive is not essential for all roles.

Applicants must have a base in Central Scotland.

They welcome new applications, as well as submissions from previous auditionees and cast members.

For further information go to [www.theatre-online.com/casting](http://www.theatre-online.com/casting?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBEwTkFPTXN5UEczVXJhbUFTSgEeRECCKL3bJvUMs0txOFuVKvAWOD03y0LoKwhZq8wcON8LtGfBqVpfUVmCmHo_aem_Rv0m_fr35reZp5KB25ZnrQ) or email casting@takeawaytheatre.co.uk.

OH NO SHIT der skal s√¶ttes nogle krydser i kalenderen nu!

Casting datoerne til den helt nye teaterforestilling ‚ÄòForvokset‚Äô er nu fundet og vi gl√¶der os vanvittigt meget! 

Datoerne for casting i Kolding er dermed d. 10. og 11. februar 2026 og d. 13. og 14. februar afholdes der casting i Helsing√∏r. 
Selve forestillingen spilles som en teaterturn√©, s√•ledes at vi spiller rundt p√• sj√¶lland. Vi h√•ber p√• at kunne f√• lov at spille flere steder, men som det ser ud nu er det Helsing√∏r vi starter i. 
Forestillingsperioden ligger i sommerferien 2026. 

Vi s√∏ger 6 skuespiller til kr√¶vende roller, samt 4 personer til ensemble. 
Forestillingen omhandler temaerne misbrug, arv og milj√∏, sorg og k√¶rlighed, og bygger p√• digte fra Janus Halds digtsamling ‚ÄòSkyggesider‚Äô.

Vi s√∏ger:
Lise (19-25 √•r) Denne rolle har stor mulighed/sansynlighed for at f√• tildelt en sang

Vivi (19-25 √•r)

Oskar (20-30 √•r)

Lise og Vivi som b√∏rn (10-15 √•r)

Oskar som barn (10-15 √•r)

Ensamble (19-30 √•r)

OBS. Er du under 18 bedes du medbringe for√¶ldre underskrift/tilladelse.

Er du ik bare mega interreseret?! 
S√• synes vi, at du skal sende en mail til oh.no.shit.kontakt@gmail.com med dit navn, din alder, et billede af dig selv, hvilken rolle du s√∏ger, samt hvor og hvorn√•r du √∏nsker at komme til casting, s√• sender vi til geng√¶ld alle de praktiske informationer din vej.
Skulle du v√¶re s√• uheldig ikke at have mulighed for at deltage fysisk nogle af casting dagene, S√Ö er der hj√¶lp at hente, for s√• kan du sende et selftape til samme mail inden d. 14. februar 2026. 

Hvis dette er tilf√¶ldet m√• du meget gerne sende en mail med de samme informationer som hvis du skulle tilmelde dig den fysiske casting, og s√• bare n√¶vne at du sender selftape- s√• har vi nemlig mulighed for at have styr p√• det hele. 

Deadline for alle tilmedlings-mails, b√•de dem der melder sig til den super hyggelige fysiske casting, og dem der melder sig til at sende selftapes, er d. 1. februar 2026.
